    <td>


<p align="center"><font size="2"><b>PSYCHOLOGICAL SKILLS TRAINING FOR PERFORMANCE
ENHANCEMENT</b></font></p>

<p align="center"><font size="2">D.E. Smith</font></p>

<p align="center"><font size="2">Nanyang Technological University,<br>
Singapore</font></p>

<p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">This presentation begins with a video of elite amateur and professional
athletes explaining their use of psychological skills training (PST) program. The basic
concept involved in PST are then explained. These strategies include relaxation, imagery,
concentration, goal setting, self-confidence development, and interpersonal skills
training. Specific means for implementing these programs with athletes are discussed.
These include conditions, which facilitate the development of sport imagery training, goal
setting training methodologies, interpersonal skill exercises, and techniques for arousal
regulation. Case study, anectodal and statistical evidence supporting the effectiveness of
pst programs with specific elite teams and athletes will follow. Finally, a brief
demonstration will support the effectiveness of these types of programs. Questions and
discussion with the audience will conclude the presentation.</font></p>
    </td>
  </tr>
